        "rich_text_8DL9Df": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Lab grown diamonds have become one of the fastest-growing choices for modern buyers who want beauty, sustainability, and value combined. Yet one question continues to surface for anyone considering a lab grown diamond engagement ring, a pair of <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/diamond-huggie-earrings\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">diamond huggie earrings</span></a>, or a timeless <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/diamond-tennis-bracelet\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">diamond tennis bracelet</span></a>: <em>What is the lab grown diamonds resale value?</em></p><p>This guide provides a clear, research-backed, easy-to-understand explanation of how resale value works, what affects it, and whether lab grown diamonds are the right choice for you.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_K7GMjk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Are Lab Grown Diamonds?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Are Lab Grown Diamonds?</h2><p>Lab grown diamonds are real diamonds created using advanced technologies such as HPHT (High Pressure High Temperature) and CVD (Chemical Vapor Deposition). They have the same physical, chemical, and optical properties as mined diamonds—because they are diamonds.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_axBwWg": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_Are_Lab_Grown_Diamonds_3cd4b4fd-f2eb-480f-9117-403da1bb8aa1.png"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bUfHBT": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Are Lab Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>What sets them apart is how they are created:</p><ul><li>More sustainable<br/></li><li>More affordable<br/></li><li>Free of mining impact<br/></li><li>Available in a wide variety of shapes and sizes<br/></li></ul><p>This affordability is a big advantage—today, you can purchase a sparkling <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/2-carat-diamond\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">2 carat diamond</span></a> lab grown stone for a fraction of the mined equivalent.</p>",
            "custom_id": "what",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JmwFBb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Do Lab Grown Diamonds Have Resale Value?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Do Lab Grown Diamonds Have Resale Value?</h2><p>The short answer: yes, lab grown diamonds do have resale value.</p><p>However, their resale value differs from natural diamonds. Lab grown diamonds typically resell at a lower percentage of their original price, mainly due to how quickly technology has reduced production costs and how new the resale market still is.</p><p>That said, demand for sustainable luxury is rising rapidly, and resale infrastructure continues to develop year after year.</p>",
            "custom_id": "do",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jc4E4r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Is the Resale Value of Lab Grown Diamonds Lower?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Is the Resale Value of Lab Grown Diamonds Lower?</h2><h3>Technological Advancements Reduce Retail Prices</h3><p>Lab grown diamonds become more affordable each year because improved technology lowers production costs. When new diamonds sell for less at retail, earlier purchases naturally depreciate faster.</p><h3>Greater Supply in the Market</h3><p>Unlike mined diamonds, lab grown diamonds are not limited by nature. Their abundance reduces scarcity, which influences resale value.</p><h3>Shifting Consumer Perception</h3><p>Although acceptance of lab grown diamonds is at an all-time high, resale buyers still lean toward natural diamonds—mainly due to tradition, not quality.</p><h3>Limited Resale Channels</h3><p>Because the lab grown diamond resale industry is still emerging, fewer jewelers buy them back. This is rapidly changing, but it affects current resale pricing.</p>",
            "custom_id": "why",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_jdz4QX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Factors That Improve Lab Grown Diamonds Resale Value",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Factors That Improve Lab Grown Diamonds Resale Value</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_ezYmxm": {
          "type": "image",
